<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key F, 3/4. Flowing hymn. LH carries open root-fifth-octave triads. RH light thirds and sixths.
- Non-diatonic notes (Eb in "^Gm7", "^A°", "^BbΔ7", etc.) resolved to nearest diatonic chord.
- ABC has many chromatic passing chords; simplified to diatonic IV, V, vi, iii for harp.
- "33" root triads predominate. "43" inversions used for color at inner voice.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- LH C2 holds through C and Am passages; rises stepwise at Gm → Dm → C cadence (bar 7).
- RH descends from F5 to C5 across bars 5-6, echoing melody.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Opens with spare two-voice RH + LH trio (bar 1-2). Fills to 4 voices LH at bar 4 climax.
- Final cadence bar 8: full F triad root position, pedal on F2.
-->
